<title>USA: Arco Chemical says 1997 to be challenging.</title>
<headline>Arco Chemical says 1997 to be challenging.</headline>
<dateline>NEWTOWN SQUARE, Pa. 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Arco Chemical on Thursday said that high material costs had compresssed margins in virtually all its businesses and anticipated that 1997 would be a challenging year due to the expiration in 1996 of fixed margin MTBE contracts.</p>
<p>&quot;Although we saw strong sales volumes in PO and derivatives, high raw material costs, coupled with weak product pricing, compressed margins in virtually all of our businesses,&quot; said Alan Hirsig, ARCO Chemical president and chief executive.</p>
